6:
S-stay back! STAY BACK! Please... I
don't wanna die!
9:
Never seen that monster before. Into
the frying pan you go!
13:
Th-thank you! I don't know who you
are, but you saved my life!
17:
Eh, don't worry about it. We're just
looking for new ingredients.
22:
Hey, Alk! This blood ain't gonna drain
itself.
25:
Ingredients? Uhh... You realize those
are monsters, right?
30:
World hopping's the best!

I wonder what you're gonna taste
like, my little noodley friend. Ooh, the
anticipation!
35:
*siiigh* Today was a good day.
Thanks for coming, guys!
40:
Man, did you see the look that guy
gave us when we were like, "we're
gonna eat the monsters"? No matter
what world we go to, people think
we're crazy.
45:
As they should. Monster Cuisine is
unnatural.
50:
That just means more hearts for me
to win over.
56:
The glass is always half-full for you,
isn't it?
61:
Always. And don't forget, Alk. After
dinner, we're taking those new
ingredients for a test-drive!
70:
Your cooking just keeps improving,
Alk.
83:
Aww... Right back atcha. You're the
best interstellar guide a girl could
ask for.
89:
Those who learn more than they
teach are the best teachers of all.
92:
When Parfait joined us, I feared our
tables would be flooded with the
meat of monsters. I am glad that
has not come to pass.
97:
Come to think of it, you haven't
served us monster at all... Right?
101:
Of course not. I'm still trying to wrap
my head around all these new
monsters, spices, and recipes.
104:
I won't serve something until I know
exactly how to cook it.
107: Spoken like a pro. Perfect or bust.
111:
There's that, but also the fact most
monsters are poisonous. If they're
not prepped right, consumption
could kill you.
115:
Look, I know you guys are on the
edge of your seat, but you're just
gonna have to wait until Alk and I
are done experimenting.
126:
Cooking monsters sounds like more
trouble than it's worth. I don't get
why you're so addicted.
130:
You prospered even as an ordinary
chef. What set you on this
outlandish path?
134:
Wait, I haven't told you yet? Okay, so
all this happened pretty recently,
but...
140:
One day, I was up in the mountains,
looking for an ultra rare ingredient
for this new dish I was creating.
143:
And I found a bunch of cool stuff, so
I just kept picking and picking...
147:
Until, before I knew it, I was
completely lost. Whoopsie, right?
150:
That is so much more than a
"whoopsie."
154: Yeah! I was totally freaking out then!
158:
I managed to survive for a while on
foraged food and emergency
rations I keep with me. But it wasn't
enough. I was on the brink of
starvation when...
167: So it was a matter of life or death.
173:
I'll never forget the taste of that
monster. I didn't have any salt or
seasonings, but even roasted plain,
it was... *siiigh*
178: They say hunger's the best sauce.
182:
I mean, I'm sure that was part of it,
but it definitely wasn't the whole
story. In that meat, I tasted... infinity.
184:
It had this flavor and texture unlike
anything I'd ever known. I started
thinking about how I could prep it,
what other ingredients it would go
with, and THAT'S when I realized... My
world would never be the same
again.
187:
It was like I'd been living in the dark,
and now, I saw the light for the first
time. And the vision revealed to me
was the future of flavor!
191:
So, yeah, that got my engines
churning, and I somehow made it
down the mountain, got into
Monster Cuisine, and never looked
back since.
204:
INSPIRATION STRIKES AGAIN! Must've
been all this reminiscing.
208:
So, who's ready for a reboot of Chow
Down Showdown?!
215:
What? You just made a case for NOT
serving us Monster Cuisine!
220:
Yeah, well, I changed my mind. I'm
just BURNING to give everyone a
taste of the future!
224:
Come on, Alk! To the kitchens! We're
gonna whip up a culinary revolution!
